reviews.text: One of the most upscale shopping mall in Kowloon. Conceirge service is good, parking friendly. Always clean and food ventilation. Washrooms are of top quality, would be great if they can add some cultural related stores like bookstores for people to grab brain food. Cinema is also comfortable

THE shopping mall in Hong Kong, with huge size, a great variety of brands (particularly in the luxury segment) and even five different themes for different areas based on the ancient Chinese elements. Good variety of food offerings as well, with plenty of hotels and transport nearby whether you prefer trains, subway, buses or taxi. The mall is new and fresh, and the overall area is very nice should you decide to take a walk nearby.
Very clean shopping mall with beautiful aesthetics. The shops were nice, and the restaurants were also nice. Definitely would recommend to tourists and travellers.
Nice place. Beautiful displays and products.  Well lit. Friendly staff. I didnt buy anything but very nice store.
Instructions inside the mall aren't clear, you have to go round and round. Shops are big but like a one way route, take you long time to get back. Get a map before you visit.

reviews.text:
프랑스의 유명 초콜릿 전문점

1977년 초콜릿의 연금술사로 불리는 로베르 랭크스(Robert Linxe)에 의해 초콜릿만을 위한 숍이 문을 열었다. 라 메종 뒤 쇼콜라는 ‘초콜릿의 방’이란 뜻으로 초콜릿의 탁월한 맛을 자랑한다. 훌륭한 초콜릿을 만들기 위해 버터 외에는 다른 식물성 기름을 넣지 않는 것이 특징이다. 클로드 르베와 같이 초콜릿 애호가 클럽에 가입한 작가 장폴 아롱은 그의 초콜릿 맛에 반해 그를 ‘가나슈의 마술사’라고 칭하기도 하였다. 초콜릿과 마카롱 맛이 뛰어나 새로운 인기 디저트 숍으로 떠오르는 곳이다.

可能點錯了，這款巧克力蛋糕頗甜。
在巴黎吃到的巧克力、閃電泡芙都非常好吃

Not the cheapest chocolate, but certainly tastes great.  Buy a small assort of macarons here after work and bring them home with you.  There is a great chance you would be able to see big smiles of your wife and family and hear a nice “thank you dad”.
Chocolate tastes rich and good
拯救世界的朱古力，老婆食完一粒之後心情好好多，多謝！

reviews.text:
Absolutely NOT an allergy friendly restaurant! 😡
I am a frequent travller and Robuchon was one of my favourite restaurants all over the world. But this branch is the worst ever Robuchon!!!😡😡😡 it’s a nightmare!! 
My husband is allergic to nuts and the waitress ensured that the chef would take precautions with food allergy. But they did not!! They caused my hubby to have an allergy reaction badly and they didn’t know allergy could kill!! I spoke to the manager and he just apologised insincerely!! My hubby just  had a bite of the dish and yes we paid for it and We paid for his medical treatment as well!! 
It stopped us going to any L'Atelier de Joël Robuchon again!!  😡😡😡

Such amazing service. We were in a hurry to go to the airport, but my parents wanted to eat something... the server didn't mind we only ordered sandwiches and kept refilling our warm water. Will need to come back and enjoy the food with more time
Fantastic place with great service. Are some great desserts here.
Nice foods, good service
Good service. Good food. Pricey.
